Preheat your oven to 200°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Pop the @British chicken breasts{2} onto a #baking tray{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Put a quarter of the @mayonnaise{32%g} into a #small bowl{}. Using the back of a #spoon{}, spread the mayo from your bowl over the top half of each breast. IMPORTANT: Discard the rest of the mayo in the bowl. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}, @Italian style herbs{1%tsp} and @olive oil{for the crumb} into another small bowl. Season with salt and pepper and mix well.

Sprinkle the crumb mixture over the mayo chicken and press it down. When the oven is hot, roast the chicken on the top shelf until cooked through and golden on top, ~{25-30%minutes}. TIP: Cover the chicken with #foil{} if the crumb is browning too quickly. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken roasts, chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Trim the @green beans{150%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{1%tbsp} and a splash of @milk{1%splash} (if you have any) and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with salt and pepper, then stir in the cheese. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

10 mins before the chicken is cooked, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Then add a splash of @water{1%splash} and immediately cover with a lid or some foil. Allow to cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

In a small bowl, mix the remaining mayo with the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and set aside. When everything is ready, slice the chicken widthways into 5 pieces and serve on your plates with the mash and beans alongside. Top with a dollop of the sweet chilli mayo to finish. Enjoy!

> If you've chosen to add bacon to your meal, add @?British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan before the beans and stir-fry until golden and crispy, 3-5 mins. Then add the beans to the bacon and continue as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.